# TypeScript Standards

## Type Definitions

- Define shared types in `src/types/index.ts`
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Avoid `any` — use `unknown` with type guards when type is uncertain
- Avoid `enum` — use `as const` objects or union types instead

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
enum PinType { FLOOD, POTHOLE }

// ✅ GOOD
const PIN_TYPES = ["flood", "pothole", "passable", "robbery"] as const;
type PinType = (typeof PIN_TYPES)[number];
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
try { await fetchPins(); } catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD
try {
  await fetchPins();
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Failed to fetch pins:", error);
  toast.error("Erro ao carregar os pontos");
  throw error;
}
```

## Imports

- Use path alias `@/` for all project imports
- Group: external libraries → `@/` project imports → relative imports
- Use named imports, avoid default exports

## Zod Schemas

- Define Zod schemas alongside form components or in `src/types/`
- Infer TypeScript types from schemas: `type FormData = z.infer<typeof formSchema>`
- Use `.safeParse()` for validation with error messages in Portuguese
